<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,624,1888]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,339,624,650]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Observations:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hack. ex Paulsen" authorityYear="1903" box="[370,876,625,651]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Calamagrostis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="emodensis" variety="breviseta">
<emphasis box="[370,694,625,650]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Calamagrostis emodensis</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[761,876,625,650]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">breviseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Paulsen, O." box="[1115,1309,625,651]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" pagination="133 - 205" refId="ref3794" refString="Paulsen, O. (1903) Plants collected in Asia-media and Persia (with 1 figure in the text). Lieutenant Olufsen's second Pamir Ekspedition. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra den Naturhistoriske Forening i Kjobenhavn 55: 133 - 205." type="book chapter" year="1903">Paulsen (1903)</bibRefCitation>
, based on Paulsen’s material from Sermut in Wakhan [Vakhan] (a territory of the former USSR, now the 
<collectingCountry name="Tajikistan" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Republic of Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
) collected during Lt. Olufsen’s second Danish Pamir Expedition in 1898 (
<bibRefCitation author="Olufsen, O." box="[1151,1318,702,728]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" refId="ref3349" refString="Olufsen, O. (1904) Through the unknown Pamirs, the second Danish Pamir expedition 1898 - 99. William Heinemann, London, 238 pp." type="book" year="1904">Olufsen 1904</bibRefCitation>
), and was based on an unpublished description by Eduard Hackel (1850–1926).
</paragraph>
